<!-- ── Page Hero ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container page-hero-inner">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">Legal</span>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: <strong>{{lastUpdated}}</strong></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ── Policy Content ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
<section class="section--sm section">
  <div class="container policy-container">

    <div class="callout callout--success" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-10);">
      <span>🛡️</span>
      <span>
        <strong>The short version:</strong> Soren is a calendar bot. It stores only the minimum data
        required to make events work. We do not sell your data, share it with advertisers, or hand
        it to third-party data brokers — ever. Your community's event information belongs to you.
      </span>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Who We Are -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Soren is a Discord bot created and operated by <strong>Toadle</strong> (operating under the
        <strong>retrac</strong> brand), a Canadian independent developer. Soren is governed by
        Canadian law and is subject to the
        <strong>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA)</strong>.
      </p>
      <p>
        For any privacy-related questions or requests, contact us at:
        <a href="mailto:info@retrac.ca">info@retrac.ca</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 2. What Data We Collect -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. What Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Soren collects and stores only the data that is strictly necessary to provide its
        calendar and events functionality. Nothing more.
      </p>

      <h3>Data stored per Discord server (guild)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Guild ID</strong> — Discord's unique identifier for your server. Used to scope all data to the correct server.</li>
        <li><strong>Event Creator Role ID</strong> — The role assigned during <code>/setup</code> that controls who can create events.</li>
        <li><strong>Premium status</strong> — Whether the server has an active Premium tier.</li>
        <li><strong>Embed color preference</strong> — The color chosen via <code>/embedcolor</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Calendar OAuth token</strong> — Only stored if you choose to connect Google Calendar via <code>/gcal connect</code>. See Section 5.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data stored per event</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Event details</strong> — Title, description, start/end time, timezone, recurrence rule, and reminder offset as entered by the event creator.</li>
        <li><strong>Channel ID and Message ID</strong> — Used to update the live event embed in Discord.</li>
        <li><strong>Creator's Discord User ID</strong> — Stored to identify who created the event.</li>
        <li><strong>Notify Role ID</strong> — If set, the role to ping when a reminder fires.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data stored per RSVP</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Discord User ID</strong> — To track who has RSVPed and in what status (accepted, tentative, declined).</li>
        <li><strong>RSVP status and timestamp</strong> — What the user clicked and when.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Data we do NOT collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> read, store, or log message content from your Discord server.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect real names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any personally identifiable information beyond Discord User IDs.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> track user behaviour, browsing habits, or activity outside of direct interactions with Soren's slash commands and buttons.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> use cookies, tracking pixels, or analytics on the Soren bot itself.</li>
        <li>We do <strong>not</strong> collect payment information. Premium purchases are handled externally and only a redemption code is passed to the bot.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 3. How We Use Data -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p>Data collected by Soren is used exclusively to provide the bot's core functionality:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Displaying event embeds in Discord with correct details and RSVP counts</li>
        <li>Sending pre-event reminder messages to the correct channel and role</li>
        <li>Maintaining live RSVP lists as users interact with event buttons</li>
        <li>Enforcing per-server settings (event creator role, embed color, premium tier)</li>
        <li>Syncing events with Google Calendar if you have chosen to connect one</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not use your data for advertising, profiling, marketing, machine learning training,
        or any purpose beyond what is listed above.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 4. Data Sharing -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h2>

      <div class="callout callout--success" style="margin:var(--space-5) 0;">
        <span>✅</span>
        <span>
          <strong>We do not sell, rent, trade, or share your data with any third-party data brokers,
          advertisers, or analytics companies. Period.</strong>
        </span>
      </div>

      <p>The only third-party service that may receive data is:</p>

      <h3>Discord</h3>
      <p>
        Soren operates through the Discord API. All bot interactions — slash commands, button clicks,
        embed updates — pass through Discord's infrastructure. Discord's own
        <a href="https://discord.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>
        governs how Discord handles that data. We have no control over Discord's data handling.
      </p>

      <h3>Google (optional — only if you connect Google Calendar)</h3>
      <p>
        If a server administrator chooses to connect a Google Calendar via <code>/gcal</code> or
        <code>/gcalint</code>, Soren will communicate with the Google Calendar API on your behalf
        using OAuth 2.0 tokens stored in the database. This data flow is:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Entirely opt-in — Google Calendar is never connected without an administrator explicitly running the connect commands</li>
        <li>Scoped to calendar read/write only — Soren cannot access your Google account, Gmail, Drive, or any other Google service</li>
        <li>Governed by <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Google Calendar integration is completely optional. The core event system works entirely
        without it.
      </p>

      <h3>Railway (website hosting)</h3>
      <p>
        This website is hosted on Railway. Railway may collect standard web server logs (IP addresses,
        request paths, timestamps) as part of normal hosting operations. These logs are not shared
        with us and are governed by
        <a href="https://railway.app/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Railway's Privacy Policy</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 5. Data Storage and Security -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>
        All Soren bot data is stored in a SQLite database on the server where the bot is hosted.
        For self-hosted deployments, data is stored entirely on the server operator's own infrastructure.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google OAuth tokens</strong> are stored encrypted in the database and are only used to authenticate requests to the Google Calendar API on behalf of the server that connected them.</li>
        <li><strong>Premium codes</strong> are stored in a flat file on the bot host and are never transmitted to users or logged publicly.</li>
        <li><strong>Bot tokens and credentials</strong> (Discord bot token, Google credentials) are stored in environment variables and are never committed to version control or exposed publicly.</li>
        <li>The Soren codebase is <strong>open source</strong> — you can review exactly what data is stored and how it is used at any time at <a href="{{githubUrl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">{{githubUrl}}</a>.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        While we take reasonable precautions to protect stored data, no system is completely
        immune to security risks. We encourage server administrators to follow Discord's own
        security best practices and to revoke any connected Google Calendar access if they
        believe their account has been compromised.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 6. Data Retention -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Data is retained for as long as it is needed to provide the bot's functionality:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Event data</strong> persists until the event is deleted via <code>/deleteevent</code> or the bot is removed from the server.</li>
        <li><strong>RSVP data</strong> is automatically deleted when the associated event is deleted (cascade delete).</li>
        <li><strong>Server configuration</strong> persists until the bot is removed from the server.</li>
        <li><strong>Google Calendar tokens</strong> persist until disconnected via <code>/gcal disconnect</code> or <code>/gcalint remove</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Premium redemption records</strong> are retained indefinitely to prevent code reuse.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If you remove Soren from your Discord server, we will delete all data associated with
        your server upon request. Contact us at <a href="mailto:info@retrac.ca">info@retrac.ca</a>
        to request a full data deletion.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 7. Your Rights (PIPEDA) -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>7. Your Rights Under PIPEDA</h2>
      <p>
        As a Canadian-operated service, Soren complies with the
        <strong>Personal Information Protection and Electronic Documents Act (PIPEDA)</strong>.
        Under PIPEDA, you have the right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access</strong> — Request a copy of any personal information we hold about you (primarily your Discord User ID and associated RSVP records).</li>
        <li><strong>Correction</strong> — Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdrawal of consent</strong> — Withdraw consent for data processing. Note that withdrawal may prevent Soren from functioning for your account.</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong> — Request deletion of your personal data from our systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Complaint</strong> — File a complaint with the Office of the Privacy Commissioner of Canada if you believe your rights have been violated.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
        <a href="mailto:info@retrac.ca">info@retrac.ca</a>.
        We will respond within 30 days.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 8. Children's Privacy -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Soren does not knowingly collect data from individuals under the age of 13, in accordance
        with Discord's own Terms of Service which require users to be at least 13 years of age.
        If you believe a child under 13 has submitted data through Soren, please contact us
        at <a href="mailto:info@retrac.ca">info@retrac.ca</a> and we will delete it promptly.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 9. Changes -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the
        "Last updated" date at the top of this page. For significant changes, we will post a
        notice in the Soren support Discord server. Continued use of Soren after changes are
        posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- 10. Contact -->
    <div class="policy-section">
      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@retrac.ca">info@retrac.ca</a></li>
        <li><strong>Discord:</strong> <a href="{{discordServer}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Join our support server</a></li>
        <li><strong>GitHub:</strong> <a href="{{githubUrl}}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open an issue</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Bottom nav -->
    <div class="policy-nav">
      <a href="/terms" class="btn btn--secondary">Read Terms of Service →</a>
      <a href="/" class="btn btn--ghost">← Back to Home</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
